OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Don Howkins
OL,5,FMr Howkins said: "When we left Bayeux
OL,6,Fwe came under heavy shellfire as we
OL,7,Fwere approaching Tilly itself and we
OL,8,Fresponded with firing back.
OL,10,F"And we were in action the best part
OL,11,Fof the time. Tilly was taken and
OL,12,Fretaken several times by us and the
OL,13,FGermans before we eventually overtook
OL,14,Fit.
OL,16,F"We were moving about all the time.
OL,18,F"When we went into action I came off
OL,19,Fmy motorbike and went on to the guns.
OL,20,FI was the gunner.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
