OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Don Howkins
OL,5,F"It was dangerous all the time. You
OL,6,Fcould come under heavy shelling or
OL,7,Fgunfire any day of the day or night.
OL,9,F"The three months I was in Normandy we
OL,10,Fhad some good times and some bad times
OL,11,Fof course but I was never really
OL,12,Ffrightened or upset at all.
OL,14,F"One thing I remember, we came across
OL,15,Fthe German gun position and they were
OL,16,Fall laying down dead except one man
OL,17,Fwas sitting in his seat still in the
OL,18,Fgun position.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
